headline: Railinc and Duke University Collaborate on Innovation to Advance Freight Rail Efficiency
summary: Railinc and Duke University's Christensen Family Center for Innovation (CFCI) today announced a new collaboration to explore practical innovations that advance freight rail safety and efficiency. The initiative will harness Duke's Product Lab, a student-led program where teams co-create solutions in rapid sprints with industry partners to deliver prototypes that have both immediate impact and long-term potential.
